Carolina Experts

UNC-Chapel Hill experts are available to provide actionable advice on a wide range of topics. If you would like to interview an expert or need help finding one, please contact a media relations representative.

View more faculty experts

  • Barbara Fredrickson is a Kenan Distinguished Professor of Psychology. Fredrickson is available to discuss her latest research on loneliness as a public health crisis and how interacting with acquaintances and strangers plays a key role in boosting well-being. Recent media clips include NBC News and the New York Times.

    Learn more

  • Sara Algoe is Director of The Love Consortium and Professor in the Department of Psychology and Neuroscience at UNC-Chapel Hill. Algoe is available to discuss science-based tips to improve relationships and the role that gratitude plays in bringing people closer together. Recent media clips includeThe Washington Post and CNN.

    Learn more

  • Rosa Li, a UNC-Chapel Hill assistant professor of psychology and neuroscience, can discuss how adolescents might be impacted by TikTok being banned. Recent media clips: Slate and WRAL.

    Learn more
